1
00:00:05,199 --> 00:00:06,160
Stanford University.

2
00:00:08,440 --> 00:00:09,100
All right,

3
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:11,000
I want to come to a new class of systems.

4
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:13,800
It was a very interesting class of systems.

5
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:14,900
They're usually called magnets,

6
00:00:14,900 --> 00:00:15,720
magnetic systems.

7
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:18,150
But they may or may not

8
00:00:18,150 --> 00:00:19,740
have anything to do with genuine magnets.

9
00:00:22,439 --> 00:00:23,800
What is a magnet?

10
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:27,020
A magnet is a collection of little magnets.

11
00:00:27,020 --> 00:00:32,540
And little magnets have the property that they point along,

12
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:35,880
they tend to align themselves along magnetic field.

13
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:38,480
But the important thing about them

14
00:00:38,480 --> 00:00:40,360
is that they're little systems which can

15
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:41,420
point in any direction.

16
00:00:43,280 --> 00:00:44,000
Furthermore,

17
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:45,180
whatever they are,

18
00:00:45,180 --> 00:00:51,000
whether they're little magnetic grains,

19
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:54,240
or are they iron atoms,

20
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:55,480
or something else.

21
00:00:55,480 --> 00:00:58,440
They are themselves little magnets.

22
00:00:58,660 --> 00:00:59,900
And it means they're like,

23
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:01,480
what do you call those things

24
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:03,060
that mariners use to figure out

25
00:01:03,060 --> 00:01:03,680
which way they're going?

26
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:04,220
Compasses,

27
00:01:04,220 --> 00:01:04,660
yes.

28
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:06,880
They're little compasses,

29
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:09,080
except they can point in three dimensional space.

30
00:01:10,040 --> 00:01:12,820
They have interactions between them.

31
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:21,180
And the interactions tend to favor parallel neighbors.

32
00:01:22,580 --> 00:01:25,460
The interactions between them are fairly similar.

33
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:26,420
They're fairly short range,

34
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:29,160
which means that roughly speaking,

35
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:30,920
each magnet affects

36
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:33,280
its nearest neighbors and tends to make

37
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:35,640
it want to align in the same direction.

38
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:38,290
That's the energy function will tend to

39
00:01:38,290 --> 00:01:40,680
be lowest when the magnets are aligned,

40
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:42,020
biggest

41
00:01:42,020 --> 00:01:43,380
when they're anti-aligned.

42
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:45,960
You can have the opposite incidentally.

43
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:48,270
You can have the situation

44
00:01:48,270 --> 00:01:50,580
where the little magnets are favor,

45
00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:52,440
the energy favors anti-alignment.

46
00:01:52,940 --> 00:01:53,580
Then,

47
00:01:53,580 --> 00:01:55,440
it's not called a parallel magnet.

48
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:58,300
A ferromagnet is a situation where they align.

49
00:01:58,540 --> 00:02:00,300
It's called an anti-ferromagnet,

50
00:02:00,300 --> 00:02:01,800
and it tends to make anti-alignment.

51
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:02,720
But real magnets,

52
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:04,240
ferromagnets,

53
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:04,920
iron magnets,

54
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:08,100
are systems where the little magnets tend

55
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:09,139
to align each other.

56
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:12,860
But they only align their nearest neighbors.

57
00:02:15,060 --> 00:02:15,620
Nevertheless,

58
00:02:15,620 --> 00:02:18,980
even though they only align their nearest neighbors,

59
00:02:18,980 --> 00:02:21,140
at sufficiently low

60
00:02:21,140 --> 00:02:21,620
temperature,

61
00:02:21,620 --> 00:02:23,410
it may be the case

62
00:02:23,410 --> 00:02:25,200
that the fluctuations are weak enough.

63
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:26,820
At very high temperatures,

64
00:02:26,820 --> 00:02:28,100
they fluctuate like mad.

65
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:30,260
At very,

66
00:02:30,260 --> 00:02:31,200
very low temperatures,

67
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:35,160
only the lowest energy states are important.

68
00:02:35,580 --> 00:02:38,010
And the lowest energy states all have

69
00:02:38,010 --> 00:02:40,440
the magnets aligned along the same direction.

70
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,320
Which direction?

71
00:02:42,540 --> 00:02:42,900
Well,

72
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:43,640
any direction,

73
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:46,320
but along the same direction.

74
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,790
So a ferromagnet is a

75
00:02:49,790 --> 00:02:52,680
system certainly which at zero temperature,

76
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:54,460
when there are no fluctuations,

77
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:56,320
tends to align.

78
00:02:56,740 --> 00:02:58,500
And it aligns by the

79
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:00,260
first one aligning the second one,

80
00:03:00,260 --> 00:03:01,940
second one aligning your third

81
00:03:01,940 --> 00:03:02,180
one,

82
00:03:02,180 --> 00:03:03,760
third one aligning the fourth one,

83
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,760
and so forth.

84
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:07,220
Or really,

85
00:03:07,220 --> 00:03:08,960
we're not thinking about a line of them.

86
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:11,260
We may be thinking about a three-dimensional block of them,

87
00:03:11,260 --> 00:03:13,340
each one aligning its neighbors,

88
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:17,000
and the whole thing in some collective way,

89
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,660
all pointing in the same direction.

90
00:03:20,060 --> 00:03:20,880
As I said,

91
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:21,580
at high temperatures,

92
00:03:21,580 --> 00:03:23,120
they tend to fluctuate wildly.

93
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:26,380
And so it's not likely that at high temperatures,

94
00:03:26,380 --> 00:03:29,000
this phenomena of alignment will persist.

95
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:31,860
We make models.

96
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:35,800
We make various kinds of models of magnets,

97
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,520
mathematical models.

98
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:38,560
The real thing,

99
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,980
the real genuine thing,

100
00:03:39,980 --> 00:03:45,000
a bunch of interacting iron atoms,

101
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,620
is much too

102
00:03:46,620 --> 00:03:47,420
hard to solve.

103
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:53,060
If for no other reason than the interactions are not...

104
00:03:53,060 --> 00:03:53,890
If for no other reason than the

105
00:03:53,890 --> 00:03:54,720
interactions are not between just nearest neighbors,

106
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:55,720
there's

107
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:57,510
a tendency for the interaction to

108
00:03:57,510 --> 00:03:59,300
slop over to second nearest neighbors,

109
00:03:59,300 --> 00:03:59,820
third nearest

110
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:00,420
neighbors.

111
00:04:00,620 --> 00:04:03,380
And this makes a nightmare of a mathematical system,

112
00:04:03,380 --> 00:04:05,980
too complicated to solve in detail.

113
00:04:06,340 --> 00:04:08,800
So we make simplified models.

114
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:13,400
The first kind of simplified model is called an...

115
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:13,840
Well,

116
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:16,519
the first kind of simplified model is

117
00:04:16,519 --> 00:04:19,200
even so simplified that it doesn't have any

118
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:20,740
interaction between its neighbors.

119
00:04:21,620 --> 00:04:22,380
All right.

120
00:04:22,380 --> 00:04:23,960
The first kind of magnet we're going

121
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:25,540
to study is not even really a magnet.

122
00:04:25,780 --> 00:04:27,900
It has no interaction between its neighbors.

123
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:31,780
But the special simplifying feature of it

124
00:04:31,780 --> 00:04:35,140
is this is a magnet whose little individual

125
00:04:35,140 --> 00:04:38,260
magnets can only point in one of two directions,

126
00:04:38,260 --> 00:04:41,180
either up or down.

127
00:04:42,780 --> 00:04:44,600
It's called a Z2 magnet.

128
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:45,900
Why Z2?

129
00:04:45,980 --> 00:04:49,060
Z2 is the group of two elements,

130
00:04:49,060 --> 00:04:50,080
up and down,

131
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:50,520
basically.

132
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:51,980
But that's not important to us.

133
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:52,360
All right.

134
00:04:52,380 --> 00:04:52,600
So we're going to study a Z2 magnet.

135
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,620
It's called a Z2 magnet.

136
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:54,840
And most studies,

137
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:56,760
or most of the early studies of magnets,

138
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:58,840
were about Z2 magnets.

139
00:04:59,140 --> 00:04:59,780
All right.

140
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:02,200
So that means we're building our magnet out

141
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:04,600
of little elements which have only two possible

142
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,100
states.

143
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:08,040
Either they're up or they're down.

144
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:11,000
And we're making an array of them.

145
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,660
We might study different kinds of models.

146
00:05:13,820 --> 00:05:16,380
We might study models in which it's a one-dimensional array.

147
00:05:16,960 --> 00:05:19,600
We might study two-dimensional arrays of them,

148
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,020
and so forth and so on.

149
00:05:22,380 --> 00:05:24,860
We might even study very high-dimensional arrays.

150
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:28,120
Not because anybody can build a high-dimensional magnet.

151
00:05:29,860 --> 00:05:32,070
It's because the mathematics of high-dimensional

152
00:05:32,070 --> 00:05:34,280
magnets turns out to be especially simple,

153
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:35,680
for reasons I'll tell you later.

154
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:36,900
All right.

155
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:39,490
So we have these systems which are

156
00:05:39,490 --> 00:05:42,060
composed of these elementary magnets which are very

157
00:05:42,060 --> 00:05:42,440
simple.

158
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:45,440
They either point up or they point down.

159
00:05:46,379 --> 00:05:49,059
And in the examples that we're

160
00:05:49,059 --> 00:05:51,740
ultimately going to want to study,

161
00:05:51,740 --> 00:05:52,360
we're going to want

162
00:05:52,380 --> 00:05:52,720
to look at the energy state of these magnets.

163
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:52,720
And in the example that we're looking at,

164
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:54,900
there's an energy function which,

165
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:55,440
let us

166
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:55,640
say,

167
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:59,360
favors neighbors being in the same direction.

168
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:00,400
All right.

169
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:04,520
So a high-energy state would

170
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:08,600
be neighboring magnets in opposite directions.

171
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:10,510
A low-energy state would be

172
00:06:10,510 --> 00:06:12,340
neighboring magnets in the same direction.

173
00:06:13,620 --> 00:06:15,340
And so at zero temperature,

174
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:18,640
which will pick out the lowest energy state,

175
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:19,880
there are only

176
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:20,740
two of them.

177
00:06:20,740 --> 00:06:25,140
Either all magnets pointing up or all magnets pointing down.

178
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:27,080
All the little elementary magnets

179
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:28,900
pointing up or all pointing down.

180
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:31,980
I'll assume for the moment that the system

181
00:06:31,980 --> 00:06:34,320
is symmetric with respect to up and down.

182
00:06:35,260 --> 00:06:37,740
If it's symmetric with respect to up and down,

183
00:06:37,740 --> 00:06:39,360
then the energy function,

184
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,460
whatever it is,

185
00:06:40,979 --> 00:06:42,440
between two neighboring magnets,

186
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:46,980
will be one thing if the two are parallel.

187
00:06:47,140 --> 00:06:47,820
In other words,

188
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:49,020
the same energy if they're

189
00:06:49,020 --> 00:06:50,220
both up or they're both down.

190
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:50,720
All right.

191
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:52,840
So if the two are parallel,

192
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:52,840
then the energy function is one

193
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:52,840
thing if they're both up or

194
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:54,690
And a higher energy if one

195
00:06:54,690 --> 00:06:56,540
is up and one is down,

196
00:06:56,540 --> 00:06:58,960
or one is down and one is up.

197
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:03,800
That's a simple system that we can try to study.

198
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:07,240
An array of them,

199
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,700
one-dimensional array,

200
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:09,660
two-dimensional array,

201
00:07:09,660 --> 00:07:10,520
three-dimensional array.

202
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:10,780
In fact,

203
00:07:10,780 --> 00:07:13,220
we could just study two atoms like this.

204
00:07:13,740 --> 00:07:14,740
We'll call them spins.

205
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,480
What they have to do with spins,

206
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:17,280
nothing is spinning.

207
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:19,380
It's just a name for them,

208
00:07:19,380 --> 00:07:20,620
spins and spins.

209
00:07:20,620 --> 00:07:20,700
And the spin is the same thing.

210
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,900
The spin is either up or down,

211
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:24,820
and the energy favors having them parallel.

212
00:07:26,470 --> 00:07:27,480
So at zero temperature,

213
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:28,780
they will all line up,

214
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:30,260
either up or down.

215
00:07:30,980 --> 00:07:32,260
Which is it going to be?

216
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:33,050
Is it going to be up

217
00:07:33,050 --> 00:07:33,780
or is it going to be down?

218
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:38,940
The answer is both are low-energy states.

219
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:41,720
So we can say they're,

220
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:42,600
well,

221
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:45,540
technically we would say the ground state is degenerate.

222
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:47,790
Two possible equal-energy ground

223
00:07:47,790 --> 00:07:49,820
states are lowest-energy states.

224
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:53,160
But that means whether it's up or

225
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:55,600
down is going to depend on minute effects,

226
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:57,080
such as,

227
00:07:57,080 --> 00:07:57,760
for example,

228
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:58,960
a tiny,

229
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:00,800
tiny stray magnetic field.

230
00:08:01,740 --> 00:08:02,720
A tiny,

231
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:03,940
tiny stray by a tiny,

232
00:08:03,940 --> 00:08:05,260
tiny stray magnetic field,

233
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:08,580
I mean some almost infinitesimally small magnetic field,

234
00:08:08,580 --> 00:08:10,060
extremely small,

235
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,660
which might even be too small to measure,

236
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:18,200
but still might favor one direction or the other.

237
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:20,080
There are so many of these little magnets.

238
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:22,870
And they're all in

239
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:25,020
this infinitesimally small magnetic field.

240
00:08:26,020 --> 00:08:28,300
And so they all line up in that direction.

241
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:31,190
If we changed this infinitesimally small

242
00:08:31,190 --> 00:08:33,720
magnetic field from up to down,

243
00:08:33,919 --> 00:08:36,080
all the spins would want to be down.

244
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:39,679
No matter how small that magnetic field is,

245
00:08:39,679 --> 00:08:41,699
the ground state will either

246
00:08:41,699 --> 00:08:43,720
be all up or all down.

247
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,840
And if we imagine a limit in

248
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:50,680
which that background magnetic field gets smaller,

249
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:51,220
and smaller,

250
00:08:51,220 --> 00:08:51,720
and smaller,

251
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:53,600
the magnetization,

252
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:56,640
the magnetization means the tendency for all the spins

253
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:59,480
to be up or all the spins to be down,

254
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,260
it doesn't go away.

255
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:03,350
It just stays there until

256
00:09:03,350 --> 00:09:06,000
the external magnetic field reverses sign,

257
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:09,000
and then they might all simultaneously reverse sign.

258
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:13,200
This is called spontaneous symmetry breaking.

259
00:09:13,660 --> 00:09:15,580
The system has a symmetry.

260
00:09:15,940 --> 00:09:16,960
What is a symmetry?

261
00:09:17,380 --> 00:09:20,180
You take all the spins and you flip them.

262
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:22,900
You turn all ups to downs.

263
00:09:23,340 --> 00:09:25,840
If you turn all ups to downs,

264
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,980
the energy stays exactly the same,

265
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:30,280
ignoring this little stray field.

266
00:09:31,340 --> 00:09:32,520
All ups have,

267
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:33,160
I mean,

268
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:34,460
they don't have to all be up.

269
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:36,400
Whatever the configuration is,

270
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:38,980
it might be one up and one down.

271
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,480
If you turn them both over,

272
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:41,980
you get one down and one up,

273
00:09:41,980 --> 00:09:42,700
same energy.

274
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,620
So this system has a symmetry.

275
00:09:45,140 --> 00:09:46,420
The symmetry being,

276
00:09:46,420 --> 00:09:49,660
let's give these degrees of freedom a name.

277
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,020
Let's call them sigma.

278
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:54,380
Sigma of I,

279
00:09:54,380 --> 00:09:56,240
the ith spin.

280
00:09:57,820 --> 00:10:00,080
And it's either plus or minus one.

281
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,360
Plus one if it's up,

282
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,900
minus one if it's down.

283
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,480
That's our system,

284
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:09,840
a collection of these simple degrees of freedom.

285
00:10:10,460 --> 00:10:11,460
The symmetry,

286
00:10:11,460 --> 00:10:12,540
here's the symmetry.

287
